HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1185
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the Peer Support Team
of the Chattanooga Police Department upon its
receipt of the Chief’s Award.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, such individuals comprise the members of the Peer Support Team of the
Chattanooga Police Department, who were recently honored with the Chattanooga Police
Department Chief's Award, in recognition of their exemplary service and dedication; and
WHEREAS, in 2025, the Peer Support Team transformed peer support within the police
department by shifting from a reactive approach to a proactive model focused on early
intervention, prevention, and sustained connection, implementing initiatives such as a peer
support watchlist and intentional check-ins to assist members before challenges escalate; and
WHEREAS, the team has further strengthened its professionalism through certification
training and the development of a Peer Support Mentor Program for cadets, fostering a culture
of wellness and trust early in a police officer's career; and
WHEREAS, members of the team have also contributed beyond traditional peer roles by
assisting with policy development, supporting the Mighty Oaks Outpost, creating wellness and
suicide awareness resources, and responding immediately after critical incidents; and
WHEREAS, the efforts of the Peer Support Team have made a lasting impact on the
Chattanooga Police Department and the well-being of its officers; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
HJR1185
016022
- 1 -

CONCURRING, that we honor and commend the Peer Support Team of the Chattanooga
Police Department upon its receipt of the Chief's Award.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
